# 📚 Survey Agent

A modern framework for automatically generating research surveys by searching arXiv papers, downloading them, and using LLMs to summarize their content. Perfect for researchers, students, and anyone who wants to stay up-to-date with the latest research! ✨

## ✅ Features

- 🔍 Search arXiv papers by keywords or specific titles
- 📥 Download PDFs and extract text content
- 🤖 Generate summaries of papers using LLMs
- 📝 Create well-formatted markdown surveys with paper lists and summaries
- 🚀 Simple and intuitive API

## 🛠️ Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/survey_agent.git
cd survey_agent
pip install -e .
```

## 🚀 Quick Start

```python
from survey_agent.arxiv import search_papers
from survey_agent.survey import generate_survey

# Search for papers with specific keywords
papers = search_papers(terms=["VLM", "Games"], max_results=10)

# Generate a survey from the papers
generate_survey(papers, output_file="game_vlm_survey.md")
```

## 📋 Usage Examples

See the `examples` directory for complete usage examples:

- `basic_search.py`: Shows how to search for papers on arXiv
- `generate_survey.py`: Demonstrates the complete workflow from search to survey generation

## 🏗️ Project Structure

```
survey_agent/
├── examples/       # Example usage scripts
└── src/
    └── survey_agent/
        ├── arxiv/  # ArXiv search and download functionality
        ├── llm/    # LLM integration for summarization
        ├── utils/  # Utility functions
        └── survey/ # Survey generation tools
```

## ⚙️ Configuration

You can configure the LLM used for summarization in the config file or by setting environment variables:

```python
# Set the LLM model to use
import os
os.environ["SURVEY_AGENT_LLM_MODEL"] = "gpt-4o"
```

